{
  "article_id": "Russell1856_HCF",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "MR. EDITOR:—It is with pleasure that I have seen your efforts to rescue from oblivion, and perpetuate in your Magazine, the many wonderful things that relate to the early history of "
      },
      {
        "text": "our State",
        "entity_key": "st_cal",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". During a residence of eight years upon "
      },
      {
        "text": "this coast",
        "entity_key": "re_calcoast",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", in which time I have explored over eighteen hundred miles of it, I have been enabled to treasure up many things in my journal which may be of interest to your many readers; I shall take pleasure in occasionally giving you an extract from it, and, as there is no time like the present, I will commence with the following:"
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Alexander Selkirk",
        "entity_key": "ase",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", the hero of Defoe's enchanting story of Robinson Crusoe, was only four years upon the "
      },
      {
        "text": "desert island of Juan Fernandes",
        "entity_key": "i_jf",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "Could we but find an author at the present day, with Defoe's graphic imagination, we believe sufficient facts of the lonely exile of ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "this woman",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " for eighteen years, could be obtained to make one of the most thrilling and beautifully descriptive volumes ever published.",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Those who are acquainted with the geography of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the coast",
        "entity_key": "re_calcoast",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", will remember that about two hundred and fifty miles south of "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Francisco",
        "entity_key": "ci_sf",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "a chain of islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " commences, called the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara Islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". While stationed upon one of "
      },
      {
        "text": "this group",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "—the island of "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Miguel",
        "entity_key": "i_sm",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "—making tidal observations for the "
      },
      {
        "text": "U. S. Government",
        "entity_key": "gov_usa",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", I was visited by "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mr. George Nediver",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", an old resident of "
      },
      {
        "text": "California",
        "entity_key": "re_local",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who came over from "
      },
      {
        "text": "the main land",
        "entity_key": "re_mld",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", on a hunting excursion, and encamped beside me, and from whom I obtained much valuable information concerning the early history of "
      },
      {
        "text": "these islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", as well as "
      },
      {
        "text": "the adjacent coast",
        "entity_key": "re_calcoast",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "One evening, while seated beside our quiet camp-fire, placidly smoking our pipes, "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mr. N.",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " related to me the following remarkable history:"
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Twenty years ago, the whole of ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indian tribes",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_NicolenoTongva",
          "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
          "natam_chumash"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " inhabiting ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "this group of islands",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " were engaged in a fierce and exterminating war with each other, and to such an extent was this deadly hostility waged that already the population had very much diminished, and would, in all probability, before many years, become entirely extinct.",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": " To prevent this, and at the same time to ameliorate the condition of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indians",
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_NicolenoTongva",
          "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
          "natam_chumash"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "the good Fathers",
        "entity_keys": [
          "aji",
          "ndur",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " of the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mission of Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "mi_santabarbaramission",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " conceived the idea of removing them to "
      },
      {
        "text": "the main land",
        "entity_key": "re_mld",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", where they might be watched over, improved, and preserved, under their immediate superintendance [sic]."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "For this purpose they visited "
      },
      {
        "text": "the islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", in company with a few "
      },
      {
        "text": "partially civilized Indians",
        "entity_key": "natam_missionindians",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and explained to them the advantages of removing to "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Mission",
        "entity_key": "mi_santabarbaramission",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ". They listened attentively to the proposal, and finally consented to go, on promises of protection from their natural enemies being given by "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Fathers",
        "entity_keys": [
          "aji",
          "ndur",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Accordingly "
      },
      {
        "text": "a small vessel",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": " was sent to "
      },
      {
        "text": "the different islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and "
      },
      {
        "text": "the various tribes",
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_NicolenoTongva",
          "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
          "natam_chumash"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " were taken one by one, to the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mission of Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "mi_santabarbaramission",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". But while "
      },
      {
        "text": "the last of the Indians",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " were embarking, at the "
      },
      {
        "text": "island of San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and all were supposed to be on board, "
      },
      {
        "text": "a child",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " was missing, and "
      },
      {
        "text": "its mother",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", in great distress was seeking everywhere, without success; each portion of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the vessel",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": " was diligently searched; all the adjacent rocks were examined, but no child could be found. Almost frantic, "
      },
      {
        "text": "the mother",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " requested "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Captain",
        "entity_keys": [
          "chu",
          "isp"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " to wait while she went into the interior to search for "
      },
      {
        "text": "her child",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", to which he reluctantly consented."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "As night closed down in darkness, heavy masses of clouds rolled up from the horizon, and gave threatening evidence of a coming storm. All were anxious for the return of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " and "
      },
      {
        "text": "her child",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", before it broke upon them, but still they came not. The wind began to blow, harder and stronger; the storm was rapidly increasing: and as "
      },
      {
        "text": "the groups of Indians",
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_NicolenoTongva",
          "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
          "natam_chumash"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " on board strained their eyes, trying to discover, in the darkness, some object that resembled "
      },
      {
        "text": "the returning woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " and "
      },
      {
        "text": "her child",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", yet saw them not, there were many sad hearts and anxious countenances that night, on their account."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The storm at last came on in all its fury, tossing ",
        "tropes": [
          12
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "their little vessel",
        "tropes": [
          12
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "up and down like a feather, and compelled them at last, though reluctantly, to put to sea for safety, before any tidings of ",
        "tropes": [
          12
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the absent ones",
        "tropes": [
          12
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "lw",
          "lwchild"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " could be received; and, although ",
        "tropes": [
          12
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the cargo of living freight",
        "tropes": [
          12
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_NicolenoTongva",
          "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
          "natam_chumash"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " reached ",
        "tropes": [
          12
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "tropes": [
          12
        ],
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " in safety, before ",
        "tropes": [
          12
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the vessel",
        "tropes": [
          12
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": " could return for ",
        "tropes": [
          12
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "tropes": [
          12
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", it was wrecked and entirely lost; and as no other could be obtained at that time, ",
        "tropes": [
          12
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the poor woman",
        "tropes": [
          12
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " had to remain upon ",
        "tropes": [
          12
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          12
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", where she lived, alone, for eighteen years; no doubt forgotten, or given up as long since dead.",
        "tropes": [
          12
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "After the discovery of gold, it was rumored that ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " was inhabited, and this, no doubt, had its foundation in the fact that several hunters of the sea otter, had seen the print of human footsteps, and they endeavored to discover the whereabouts of the individuals, but could not: yet, as all the footprints were alike, they concluded that there could be ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "only one person",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " living upon it; and many attempts were made to find out who, and where ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "this strange being",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " was, but without avail, until one of California's oldest pioneers, ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Mr. Nediver",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "—the gentleman who related to me the story, and who arrived in ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "this country",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_local",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "some twenty-five years ago, and still resides at ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "—went over to look for her, and who, having spent many years as a hunter, and trapper in ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Rocky Mountains",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_rockies",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", was as expert as an Indian, in following a trail, and consequently found but little difficulty in discovering the track, which he followed until he saw a singular object among the rocks upon the sea shore, near the mouth of a ravine, upon its knees, engaged in skinning a seal. ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Upon approaching, he found it to be ",
        "tropes": [
          4,
          1
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a woman",
        "tropes": [
          4,
          1
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " clad in a singular dress of feathers; and, when she saw him, she jumped up, and with excessive joy ran towards him, and seemed almost beside herself with wild delight, at the sight, once more, of a human being.",
        "tropes": [
          4,
          1
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "In her hand she held a rude knife-blade, that she had made from a piece of old iron, probably obtained from the fragment of some wreck, and which she evidently valued beyond anything else in her possession."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "She was unable to make herself understood, except by signs; in making which she showed a great amount of intelligence, and signified her willingness to accompany him to ",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ],
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": " Here ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Father Gonzales",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "jru",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", of ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Mission",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "mi_santabarbaramission",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", took the greatest pains to discover some of ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indians",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_NicolenoTongva",
          "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
          "natam_chumash"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " who had been taken from ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "those islands",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", eighteen years before, but not one of them could be found, and what became of them, is a mystery unto this day.",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Not one of the Indians within a circumference of many miles, could be found, who could understand her. So that she could communicate only by signs.",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "It appears from her narative [sic], that after leaving ",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the vessel",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": " in search of ",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "her child",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ],
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", she wandered about for several hours, and when she found it, the wild dogs which infest ",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", even to the present day, had killed, and nearly devoured it.",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": " We can better imagine the feelings of a mother at such a time, than describe them. When she returned to the spot where she had left "
      },
      {
        "text": "the vessel",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": " tell of her sorrows, for the loss of "
      },
      {
        "text": "her child",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", that too was gone, and was bearing away her kindred and friends from her sight."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Could she have realized, then, that for eighteen long years she must live alone in the world, without one kind word of comfort, one cheering look from a friendly eye, or one smile of recognition, it would have been too much for even her wild, but womanly nature to bear, and with her, as with us, it is well that we know not the future."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "From day to day, she lived in hope, beguiling the weary hours in providing for her wants. With snares made of her hair she caught birds; and with the skins, properly prepared, she made her clothing; her needles were neatly made of bone, and cactus thorns; her thread was of sinews from the seal: in these, and many other articles found in her possession, she exhibited much of the native ingenuity she possessed."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Whether she still remembered her own language or not, will forever remain a mystery. "
      },
      {
        "text": "She was very gentle, and kind, especially to children, and nothing seemed to please her more than to be near them: and ",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the poor woman",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " would often shed tears, while attempting to describe, by signs, ",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "her own little one",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "which had been killed and eaten by the wild dogs.",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The sympathy felt for her welfare, caused the people to supply her, bountifully, with everything she needed; and, very imprudently, allowed her to eat almost anything she chose, and the result was, that in about six months after her escape from her lonely exile she sickened and died—having, undoubtedly, been killed with kindness."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "At the conclusion of the old gentle man's tale, I was more than ever convinced of the truthfulness of the remark, that \"Truth is stranger than fiction.\""
      }
    ]
  ]
}